<ref target="/wiki/Henceforward..." title="Henceforward...">Henceforward...</ref>(1987)

<p>A Small Family Business is a play by <ref target="/wiki/Alan_Ayckbourn" title="Alan Ayckbourn">Alan Ayckbourn</ref> about the eponymous business and dealing with the <ref target="/wiki/Thatcherism" title="Thatcherism">Thatcherism</ref> of the time. It premiered at the Olivier stage of the <ref target="/wiki/Royal_National_Theatre" title="Royal National Theatre">Royal National Theatre</ref> on 20 May 1987, where it won the <ref class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Evening_Standard_Award" title="Evening Standard Award">Evening Standard Award</ref> for Best Play for that year. Its Broadway premiere occurred on 27 April 1992.</p>

